Secondly, I grant that strange words invented out of vanity and curiosity by the boldness of a private spirit, are to be rejected but not such words which have been approved, & long used in the Catholick Church, and which warrantable and just necessity hath brought into the world; 

                           ••
                        one do wrangle about words but deluded men which do deny the mysteries signified by them, and are enemies to the Truth, saith S. Hilary de Synodis. I answer then and say:
